==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aarons rod
<hw>Aar"on's rod`</hw> <pr>(⟦acir⟧r"⟦ucr⟧nz r⟦ocr⟧d`)</pr>. <ety>[See
Exodus vii. 9 and Numbers xvii. 8]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>A rod with one serpent twined around it, thus differing from the
caduceus of Mercury, which has two.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant with a tall flowering
stem; esp. the great mullein, or hag-taper, and the
golden-rod.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>AAS</ent>⟦br⟧
